Initialize dev environment:
----------------------
1) Create virtualenv
   $ virtualenv -p /usr/bin/python3.5 virtualenv
   $ source virtualenv/bin/activate

2) Install packages
   $ pip install -e .


Load dev environment:
-----------------------
Load virtualenv:
$ source virtualenv/bin/activate


Upload to pip:
-----------------------
$ rm -rf dist
$ python setup.py sdist
$ python setup.py bdist_wheel
$ twine upload dist/*


Creating new fixtures:
-----------------------
$ tar --preserve-permissions --atime-preserve -cJvf myfixture_cryfs_data.tar -C /path/to/datadir .
$ cryfs /tmp/basedir /tmp/mountdir
# TODO use --same-owner, but then the test cases need sudo rights ... :(
$ tar --preserve-permissions --atime-preserve -C /tmp/mountdir -xvf myfixture_cryfs_data.tar
$ fusermount -u /tmp/mountdir
$ tar --preserve-permissions --atime-preserve -cvf myfixture_cryfs_encoded.tar -C /tmp/basedir .
